  "title": "Principal Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Years of Experience</strong></p><p><strong>11–16 years</strong></p><p><strong>Minimum Qualifications</strong></p><p>· Bachelor’s Degree in Engineering / Electronics / Computer Science</p><p>· Postgraduate qualification in AI / ML preferred</p><p><strong>Required Skills</strong></p><p>· Cloud Architecture (AWS, Azure, GCP)</p><p>· Trading Systems Architecture</p><p>· Kafka & Cassandra</p><p>· Distributed Systems</p><p>· CI/CD (Jenkins, Azure DevOps)</p><p>· Kubernetes / OpenShift</p><p>· Low-latency systems</p><p>· DR / BCP Planning</p><p>· Release & Change Governance</p><p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p><strong>Role Overview</strong><br />Sr. Engineer will be responsible for designing, modernising, and governing mission-critical, low-latency platforms with a strong focus on cloud migration, distributed systems, and release governance for enterprise-scale systems.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>· Architect and modernise mission-critical platforms across cloud and hybrid environments</p><p>· Lead cloud migration initiatives across AWS, Azure, and GCP</p><p>· Design and operate low-latency, high-availability distributed systems</p><p>· Own Kafka messaging architecture and Cassandra data platforms</p><p>· Lead CI/CD transformation and release automation initiatives</p><p>· Govern production releases, DR/BCP exercises, and platform resiliency</p><p>· Provide technical leadership across cross-functional engineering teams</p>",
